		<![CDATA[     Summertime is hot in Egypt, so pack light clothing. But be sure to bring warm-weather clothing that is also modest. If you visit a mosque shorts are definitely out of the question, for both men and women. In mosques, women should wear longer skirts and a head covering, usually a scarf. And the upper part of their arms should be covered with sleeves. For touring other wonderful sights and historical places, casual, comfortable clothing is fine for both men and women.]]>
